SUMMARY:Sisters Country Half/50K Field Trip
DESCRIPTION:Northwest Trail Runners\n**Distance**: Half-Marathon or 50k trail run\n**Gain**: 700 ft (Half)/2400 ft (50k)\n**Drive time from PDX:** Approx. 3 hours\n**After:** Post race burrito bar and beer from [Cascade Lakes Brewing](https://www.cascadelakes.com) will be available following the race for participants and volunteers.\n\nSeveral of us at NWTR have decided to sign up for the Sisters Country Half on May 3rd. We recommend signing up ASAP as spots fill up fast!\n\nUltraSignup Link: https://ultrasignup.com/register.aspx?did=127686\n\nThis is an official race (not sanctioned by us) that you will need to go and ***sign up for on your own***.\n\nThis posting is to give us an idea of who from the group is attending and to post our chat and photos.\n\n**Please make your own arrangements for Saturday if you are planning to stay overnight.**\n\nMore details can be found at their webpage [Sisters Country Spring 50K & Half Marathon](https://www.alpinerunning.co/sisters-country) for course descriptions\, maps\, videos\, elevation profiles\, information about the start/finish\, and other info!\n\nRemember\, register yourself **first**\, then come back here for the fun chat before the race and amazing photos afterwards!\n\nHosted by: ALPINE RUNNING
